OL,7,FFollowing the crash, Network Rail said
OL,8,Fone of its railhead treatment trains `
OL,9,Fwhich tackle autumn leaf fall ` ran
OL,10,Falong the line and passing loop the
OL,11,Fnight before the crash.
OL,13,FLeaves cause major disruption every
OL,14,Fautumn when they stick to damp rails
OL,15,Fand become compressed by train wheels.
OL,16,FThis creates a smooth, slippery layer
OL,17,Fsimilar to black ice on roads,
OL,18,Freducing trains' grip.
